===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
{{Han compound|ls=ic|甲|𠂇|t1=fan|t2=hand}} - a man holding a fan, indicating that he is a servant.

===Etymology===
Note similarities to {{cog|my|ပေ|t=to be soiled, dirty}}.

The Mandarin pronunciation ''bēi'' differs from the expected pronunciation ''bī'' (carrying forward from Middle Chinese pjie) due to homophony avoidance with the vulgar word {{m|zh|屄|t=cunt}}.

